A 63 - year - old Dover woman has died from injuries she sustained in a May 12 crash with a state police cruiser on U.S. 113 south of Georgetown , state police said Monday .
Anezia Valette was a passenger in a car driven by Marie Voltaire , 37 , of Dover .

A0: a May 12 crash with a state police cruiser
RelatedSentence: The crash , reported at 3:37 p.m. , happened as Voltaire , driving a 1999 Toyota Corolla , was southbound in the right lane on Du Pont Boulevard ( U.S. 113 ) , just north of Speedway Road .

For an unknown reason , the Corolla drifted into the left lane , the left turn lane , and then onto the grass median , where it struck a marked Delaware State Police 2013 Chevrolet Tahoe head on , Cpl. John Day said .

The trooper was taken by ambulance to Beebe Medical Center in Lewes where he was treated for minor injuries and released .
Voltaire and her passenger , Valette , both were taken to Nanticoke by ambulance .
The occupants of both vehicles were properly restrained at the time of the crash , Day said .
Police are continuing investigation into the crash .
